<a name="DESCRIPTION" id="DESCRIPTION"></a>
<h1><span class="mw-headline"><span id="description">DESCRIPTION</span></span></h1>
<p>Here's some normal text. It includes text that is <strong>bolded</strong>, <em>italicized</em>, <ins>underlined</ins>, and <code>code</code>-formatted.</p>
<a name="An_Example_List" id="An_Example_List"></a>
<h2><span class="mw-headline"><span id="an_example_list">An Example List</span></span></h2>
<ul>
<li><strong><span id="item_this_is_a_bulleted_list_2e">This is a bulleted list.</span></strong></li>
<li><strong><span id="item_here_27s_another_item_2e">Here's another item.</span></strong></li>
</ul>
<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:182px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Example.png" class="image" title="Figure 1."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/70/Example.png/180px-Example.png" width="180" height="194" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Example.png" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Figure 1.</div>
</div>
</div>
<pre>
   Here's some embedded HTML.  In this block I can 
   include images, apply <span style="color: green">
   styles</span>, or do anything else I can do with
   HTML.  pod parsers that aren't outputting HTML will
   completely ignore it.
</pre>
